First Quantum Awaits Approval to Start on Zambia Mine, Post Says

-- B y   A n t h o n y   M u k w i t a
-- 
2011-05-28T09:09:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-28/first-quantum-awaits-approval-to-start-on-zambia-mine-post-says.html
First Quantum Minerals Ltd. (FM)  is
awaiting approval from an Environmental Impact Statement before
starting to dig for copper at its $1 billion Trident project in
Kalumbila, north western  Zambia , the Post reported, citing
company spokesman Godfrey Msiska.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anthony Mukwita in Lusaka at 
 amukwita1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 